OL,6,FWouldn't it be nice if human behaviour
OL,7,Fwere simple? If you could just turn a
OL,8,Fdial here or there, increasing the
OL,9,Flevel of this or that hormone in our
OL,10,Fbrains, and change the way we behave?
OL,12,FThe way people talk about hormones, you
OL,13,Freally would think it was this easy. At
OL,14,Fa recent antenatal class, my wife and I
OL,15,Fheard all about the endless benefits of
OL,16,Foxytocin; the concept of a "dopamine
OL,17,Fhit" is common knowledge; and that
OL,18,Fsomeone's behaviour can be explained by
OL,19,Ftheir being "hormonal" is a standard,
OL,20,Feveryday notion.
OL,3,CWhat science tells us about the real
OL,4,Cimpact of hormones on our minds
